&lt;div class=&quot;content-intro&quot;&gt;&lt;p&gt;Founded in 2000, FAM Brands designs, manufactures, and sells men’s and women’s sportswear and active wear apparel to major retailers, big box stores, and specialty boutiques&amp;nbsp;across the country and throughout the world.&amp;nbsp;Our portfolio of proprietary brands features Marika, Wildfox, Three Dots, and Balance Collection, while a partial list of licensing partners includes Orvis, Jessica Simpson, Eddie Bauer, and Woolrich.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;With the capacity to produce over 75 million units per year, our mission continues to be making top-quality apparel accessible to everyone at an impressive value and an irresistible price.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;That&#39;s the FAM Brands difference.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Product Developer – Women’s Sportswear&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Position Summary&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Product Developer plays a key role in bringing products from concept to production by partnering with Product Management, Design, Merchandising and global vendor teams. This position requires exceptional attention to detail, strong organizational skills, and the ability to manage multiple brands, development calendars and vendor relationships in a fast-paced environment.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Key Responsibilities&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Manage day-to-day product development activities across multiple brands, seasons and vendor partners.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Track development milestones and ensure adherence to seasonal calendars.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Partner with Product Manager, Design and Merchandising teams throughout the development process.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Review lab dips (L/D), strike-offs (S/O), trims, and development submissions; communicate comments and approvals to vendors.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Evaluate color submissions and ensure alignment with brand standards.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Support development of prints, graphics, embellishments, washes and specialty treatments.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Identify and resolve development, construction and quality issues.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Materials, Costing &amp;amp; Vendor Management&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Lead or support fabric and trim sourcing initiatives aligned with brand identity and target costs.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Partner with Product Manager and Design/Merch teams to support costing goals.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Collaborate with vendors and internal teams to balance quality, design intent and cost requirements.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Manage vendor communications, development timelines, approvals and issue resolution.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;PLM, Samples &amp;amp; Data Management&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Maintain accurate product information, BOMs, approvals and development records within Centric PLM.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ensure seasonal data, sample tracking, and documentation are organized and up to date.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Track inbound and outbound development packages and samples, including receipt, distribution and follow-up.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Maintain organized seasonal sample archives and material libraries.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Cross-Functional Collaboration &amp;amp; Process Improvement&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Partner with Design, Merchandising, Sales, and Technical Design teams to support product execution.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Participate in SMS reviews, milestone meetings and seasonal development meetings.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Identify opportunities to improve workflows, SOPs and team efficiency.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Contribute to a collaborative, team-oriented culture focused on continuous improvement

&lt;div class=&quot;content-intro&quot;&gt;&lt;p&gt;Founded in 2000, FAM Brands designs, manufactures, and sells men’s and women’s sportswear and active wear apparel to major retailers, big box stores, and specialty boutiques&amp;nbsp;across the country and throughout the world.&amp;nbsp;Our portfolio of proprietary brands features Marika, Wildfox, Three Dots, and Balance Collection, while a partial list of licensing partners includes Orvis, Jessica Simpson, Eddie Bauer, and Woolrich.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;With the capacity to produce over 75 million units per year, our mission continues to be making top-quality apparel accessible to everyone at an impressive value and an irresistible price.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;That&#39;s the FAM Brands difference.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;SOME OF WHAT YOU&#39;LL DO&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;div&gt;Support the design process for assigned category, from concept to final product.&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;div&gt;Maintain all style and design information in Centric PLM.&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;div&gt;Collaborate with the sales, senior design, and merchandising teams to conceptualize and develop new product ideas.&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;div&gt;Create design presentations and product specs for new product lines using the PLM system.&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;div&gt;Research and stay up-to-date on trends in the industry.&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;div&gt;Create detailed technical drawings and specifications for products using the PLM system.&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;div&gt;Collaborate with vendors to ensure that products are manufactured to specification.&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;div&gt;Participate in fit sessions to ensure that products meet design and quality standards.&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;WHAT YOU&#39;LL NEED TO SUCCEED&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;div&gt;Bachelor&#39;s degree in a related field such as fashion design, textiles, or product design.&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;div&gt;4+ years of experience in design.&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;div&gt;Proficiency in Adobe Creative Suite, particularly Illustrator and Photoshop.&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;div&gt;Strong attention to detail and ability to multitask in a fast-paced environment.&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;div&gt;Experience with PLM systems is a must for this role.&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;div&gt;Experience in the mass market and licensed brands is a plus.&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;div&gt;Excellent communication and collaboration skills.&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;div&gt;A portfolio of relevant design work is required.&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;content-pay-transparency&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;pay-input&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;description&quot;&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size: 22px;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;text-decoration: underline;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;COMPENSATION&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
