&lt;div class=&quot;content-intro&quot;&gt;&lt;p&gt;Founded in 2000, FAM Brands designs, manufactures, and sells men’s and women’s sportswear and active wear apparel to major retailers, big box stores, and specialty boutiques&amp;nbsp;across the country and throughout the world.&amp;nbsp;Our portfolio of proprietary brands features Marika, Wildfox, Three Dots, and Balance Collection, while a partial list of licensing partners includes Orvis, Jessica Simpson, Eddie Bauer, and Woolrich.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;With the capacity to produce over 75 million units per year, our mission continues to be making top-quality apparel accessible to everyone at an impressive value and an irresistible price.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;That&#39;s the FAM Brands difference.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Position Overview&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Design Coordinator provides administrative and organizational support to the Design team, helping ensure seasonal development materials are prepared, organized, and communicated efficiently. This role works closely with the VP of Design to coordinate fabric and trim development, maintain seasonal libraries, manage sample organization, and support key milestones throughout the product development calendar.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This is an excellent entry-level opportunity for someone interested in apparel design, textiles, sourcing, and product development who thrives in a fast-paced environment and enjoys managing details and processes.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Key Responsibilities&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Coordinate and maintain seasonal fabric and trim libraries, including fabric headers, trim headers, swatches, and development materials.&lt;/li&gt;
